Votes are the oldest known ethnic group in Ingria. They are probably descended from Iron-age population of north-eastern Estonia and western Ingria. Some scientists claim that they were tribe of Estonians, who became different peoples because of isolation from other Estonians. It is speculated that ancient Estonian county of [[Vaiga]] got its name from Votians.<ref name="ERM"/> The [[Budini]], ancient people described by [[Herodotus]], have been identified as Votes. The [[Kylfings]], a people active in Northern Europe during the [[Viking Age]], may have also been Votes.
